messages.content: ComfyUI_InterpolateEverything is a custom node for interpolating between elements in Stable Diffusion ComfyUI.
What is the current functionality of ComfyUI_InterpolateEverything?
The current functionality of ComfyUI_InterpolateEverything is to create a preprocessed ControlNet OpenPose input midway between two input images, referred to as Interpolate Poses.
What future features are planned for ComfyUI_InterpolateEverything?
A planned future feature is Interpolate Lineart, which will use motion interpolation to create line-art ControlNet inputs midway between two input images.

To install ComfyUI_InterpolateEverything, first install the comfyui_controlnet_aux repository, then clone the ComfyUI_InterpolateEverything repository to the custom_nodes directory of your ComfyUI installation.
ComfyUI_InterpolateEverything has a dependency on comfyui_controlnet_aux.
What will happen if comfyui_controlnet_aux is not installed?
If comfyui_controlnet_aux is not installed, InterpolateEverything is likely to fail to load.
